s/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-desk-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-desk-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-desk-070725-1050-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"Color ties the house together, with blue, coral, and yellow tones appearing throughout. In the sunlit kitchen, cabinetry painted in Farrow \u0026amp; Ball\u0026#39;s Hague Blue No. 30 anchors the room. A central island, topped with black walnut and supported by custom steel legs, blends function with elegance. Nearby, the home office area echoes the color scheme, creating continuity in daily-use spaces.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-070725-1050-01-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-kitchen-070725-1050-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBoth children’s rooms feature sleeping areas and built-in desks. In one, Schumacher butterfly wallpaper adds a whimsical, unexpected flourish to the otherwise clean mid-century aesthetic, delighting one of the family’s daughters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1279\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"This children\u0026#39;s bedroom features sleeping areas and built-in desks. Schumacher butterfly wallpaper adds a whimsical, unexpected flourish to the otherwise clean mid-century aesthetic, delighting one of the family’s daughters.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-01-940x626.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-01-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1289\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-02.jpg\" alt=\"This children\u0026#39;s bedroom features sleeping areas and built-in desks. Schumacher butterfly wallpaper adds a whimsical, unexpected flourish to the otherwise clean mid-century aesthetic, delighting one of the family’s daughters.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-02-940x631.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-02-800x537.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-02-768x516.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-02-1536x1031.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe second bedroom introduces leaf-patterned wallpaper with a natural motif reminiscent of mid-century woodblock prints. The design feels timeless, reinforcing a quiet connection to nature.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-03.jpg\" alt=\"This bedroom introduces leaf-patterned wallpaper with a natural motif reminiscent of mid-century woodblock prints. The design feels timeless, reinforcing a quiet connection to nature.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-03.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-03-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-03-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-03-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bedroom-070725-1050-03-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe children’s bathroom benefits from a new light well that brings daylight deep into the space. A custom vanity and cabinetry by Gustave Carlson keep the space functional, yet elevated.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1279\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bathroom-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"The children’s bathroom benefits from a new light well that brings daylight deep into the space. A custom vanity and cabinetry by Gustave Carlson keep the space functional, yet elevated.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bathroom-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bathroom-070725-1050-01-940x626.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bathroom-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bathroom-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-childrens-bathroom-070725-1050-01-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the primary suite, a display ledge and sliding barn door, both crafted from Western Red Cedar, offer thoughtful detailing. The barn door encloses a cozy sitting area, which opens via floor-to-ceiling retractable Fleetwood glass doors to the garden beyond.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"In the primary suite, a display ledge and sliding barn door, both crafted from Western Red Cedar, offer thoughtful detailing. The barn door encloses a cozy sitting area, which opens via floor-to-ceiling retractable Fleetwood glass doors to the garden beyond.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-01-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1273\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-02.jpg\" alt=\"In the primary suite, a display ledge and sliding barn door, both crafted from Western Red Cedar, offer thoughtful detailing. The barn door encloses a cozy sitting area, which opens via floor-to-ceiling retractable Fleetwood glass doors to the garden beyond.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-02-940x623.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-02-800x530.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-02-768x509.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bedroom-070725-1050-02-1536x1018.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe primary bathroom uses ceramic tile for a clean, tactile floor surface. Custom cabinetry and a green vanity anchor the space, while blue wall tiles add a calming tone, extending the home’s signature palette.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"2400\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"The primary bathroom uses ceramic tile for a clean, tactile floor surface. Custom cabinetry and a green vanity anchor the space, while blue wall tiles add a calming tone, extending the home\u0026#39;s signature palette.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01-940x1175.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01-1229x1536.jpg 1229w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-01-1638x2048.jpg 1638w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-02.jpg\" alt=\"The primary bathroom uses ceramic tile for a clean, tactile floor surface. Custom cabinetry and a green vanity anchor the space, while blue wall tiles add a calming tone, extending the home\u0026#39;s signature palette.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-02-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-02-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-02-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-primary-bathroom-070725-1050-02-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe guest bedroom echoes the primary suite with another custom art ledge in Western Red Cedar, stained to reveal the wood’s natural grain. It’s a subtle, repeating gesture that unifies rooms across the home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-guest-bedroom-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"The guest bedroom has an art ledge in Western Red Cedar, stained to reveal the wood’s natural grain. It’s a subtle, repeating gesture that unifies rooms across the home.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-guest-bedroom-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-guest-bedroom-070725-1050-01-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-guest-bedroom-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-guest-bedroom-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-guest-bedroom-070725-1050-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eNear the entrance, a thoughtfully designed mudroom reflects the husband’s British heritage. With individual storage for each family member, Carlson’s custom cabinetry blends tradition with everyday functionality.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-01.jpg\" alt=\"Near the entrance, a thoughtfully designed mudroom with blue cabinetry has individual storage for each family member.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-01.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-01-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-01-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-01-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02.jpg\" alt=\"Near the entrance, a thoughtfully designed mudroom with blue cabinetry has individual storage for each family member.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02-940x940.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02-800x800.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02-200x200.jpg 200w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02-768x768.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/remodeled-eichler-interior-mudroom-070725-1050-02-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis reimagined Eichler is more than a renovation; it’s a dialogue between eras. Gustave Carlson’s thoughtful design honors the home’s architectural legacy while tailoring it for the rhythms of contemporary family life. Every detail, from custom cabinetry to curated color, reflects a commitment to craft, comfort, and connection. Bathed in natural light and filled with art, the house stands as a timeless expression of modern living rooted in optimism.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by \u003ca href=\"https://www.davidduncanlivingston.com/\"\u003eDavid Duncan Livingston\u003c/a\u003e | Architecture, interior and custom cabinetry design: Gustave Carlson Design | Interior Design and Decoration: Atelier Davis | Landscaping: Groundcover Landscaping| Construction: Flegel’s Construction\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
